			<ns0:name>b...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/105821748722532785568/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">this is a shm fd that only allows MAP_READ but not MAP_WRITE, rather than a read-only file fd that should be mmap'd MAP_READ but not MAP_WRITE.  i think mseaborn wants a way to take a shm fd -- which must be r/w initially -- and derive a ro-shm fd from it, so that he can pass it to some process that he doesn't trust to not overwrite the data, but should have read access to it.

this would require a new descriptor (sub)type or attribute.  no unixes have similar capabilities afaik, so it's an interesting feature request, but not something we need to promise anybody.  no code uses such a feature.  moving to milestone-z.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2010-10-29T19:58:12.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2010-10-29T19:58:12.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:updates>
